<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900501-0067</DOCNO><DOCID>900501-0067.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Forest Oil Corp.:   Gas Write-Down to Result   In Loss for First Quarter</HL><DATE>05/01/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10</SO><CO>   FOIL</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Forest Oil Corp. said it will write down $84 million inoil and gas reserves, reducing first-quarter earnings by $55million and resulting in a loss for the quarter.   Forest Oil said the write-down is primarily attributableto a significant decrease in the spot market price of naturalgas between January and March. The Denver-based company saidit sells 80% to 90% of its natural gas on the spot market.The company also attributed the write-down to a revision inreserves and production-rate estimates on Gulf of Mexicoproperties.</LP><TEXT>   In the first quarter last year, Forest Oil had net incomeof $1.8 million, or 5 cents a share, on revenue of $63.9million. Those earnings included a $12 million write-down ofoil and gas properties.</TEXT></DOC>